The cocooning scene from _Alien_, cut from the original release, is possibly the most harrowing scene [not\] in the film. It was supposed to feature towards the end of the movie, when Ripley is already the last remaining crew member alive, or at least we’re led to assume. This cut scene follows a flame-thrower toting Ripley into the Alien’s hive. Here, she finds crew members Dallas and Brett either metamorphosing into or being consumed by an enclosing egg. Dallas is barely alive enough to plead to Ripley to kill him, which she is reluctant to do but ultimately obliges.

The Youtube channel Alien Theory has published a deep dive into the scene including the various explanations for why the scene was cut, not least pacing. But had it remained, would it have swayed James Cameron away from introducing a queen and drones concept in the sequel _Aliens_?

